        <updateDate>2013-07-20T16:36:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Small Business Job Protection Act of 2013 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code, as amended by the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act, to redefine "applicable large employer," for purposes of the mandate requiring employers to provide health insurance for their employees, to mean an employer with at least 100 full-time employees (currently, 50).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
